
  INSTALL
  -------

  As simple as:

    # python setup.py install

  (Probably you will need python-dev package of your favorite distro).


  UNINSTALL
  ---------

  Reddo will be installed in:

    $(prefix)/bin/reddo
    $(prefix)/share/reddo/reddolib/
    $(prefix)/share/doc/reddo/
    $(prefix)/share/man/man1/reddo.1.gz
    /etc/reddo/


  RPM PACKAGES
  ------------

  Just execute:

    # python setup.py bdist_rpm


  DEBIAN PACKAGES
  ---------------

  If you are a debian|ubuntu user, probably you prefer to build your
  own debian package. Just usu:
  
    # dpkg-buildpackage
  
  (from dpkg-dev package) in order to generate reddo deb packages.


  APT REPOSITORY
  --------------

  Also, there are debian packages at this apt reposity:

    [ -- /etc/apt/sources.list -- ]
    deb http://reddo.sourceforge.net/ debian/
    deb-src http://reddo.sourceforge.net/ debian/

  You know the drill:

    # apt-get install reddo

  If you want to take a look at the source package:

    # apt-get source reddo


